More than half of the world's coral reefs are endangered due to pollution, overfishing, and human activities.
The World Conservation Union (IUCN) will release a report on this issue soon.
The destruction of reefs will impact over a billion people.
Human actions, climate change, and invasive species are causing reef depletion.
Recovery could take decades to centuries.
Artificial reefs are being created to enhance fishery resources.
The coral reefs in South Asia are struggling to recover from past damage.
The devastation caused by tsunamis may take centuries to heal, affecting marine life profoundly.
